WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.012 --> 00:00:14.890
And though we are sad to lose her.

2
00:00:15.766 --> 00:00:20.354
we can be joyful in the knowledge
that her soul is at peace.

3
00:00:21.480 --> 00:00:23.732
Now. I'd like to read an excerpt
from the benediction.

4
00:00:25.484 --> 00:00:31.698
"Our help is in the name of the Lord
who made heaven and earth.

5
00:00:36.453 --> 00:00:38.120
- Hey. Liz.
- <i>Hey. babe.</i>

6
00:00:38.121 --> 00:00:39.665
How're you doing?

7
00:00:40.290 --> 00:00:41.875
Shit. I don't know. I'm okay.

8
00:00:42.376 --> 00:00:44.545
I'm at Maya's funeral
paying my respects. but…

9
00:00:45.671 --> 00:00:49.215
…trying to give everybody some space
and just. you know. stay inconspicuous.

10
00:00:49.216 --> 00:00:50.758
Well. that's impossible.

11
00:00:50.759 --> 00:00:54.512
You're a gorgeous six-foot-tall woman
who dresses like human Funfetti.

12
00:00:54.513 --> 00:00:58.224
Well. I am in all black today.
but my underwear's neon green

13
00:00:58.225 --> 00:01:00.810
and there's a snake eating a tiger
across my ass 'cause I got to do me.

14
00:01:00.811 --> 00:01:02.770
Of course you do. And you're perfect.

15
00:01:02.771 --> 00:01:03.855
<i>Any more news?</i>

16
00:01:03.856 --> 00:01:07.817
Yeah. a toxicology report tested positive
for alcohol and Xanax in her system

17
00:01:07.818 --> 00:01:09.069
with OxyContin to boot.

18
00:01:09.862 --> 00:01:13.323
And we still don't know if it was
an accident or not. They may never…

19
00:01:13.991 --> 00:01:18.035
Oh. shit. Hey. Liz. someone saw me.
They're waving me over.

20
00:01:18.036 --> 00:01:20.288
Just pretend you're there
seeing someone else.

21
00:01:20.289 --> 00:01:21.290
What? Okay.

22
00:01:25.836 --> 00:01:27.795
<i>You're being real quiet.</i>

23
00:01:27.796 --> 00:01:29.173
You doing something weird?

24
00:01:29.756 --> 00:01:30.882
I sure am.

25
00:01:30.883 --> 00:01:31.884
<i>All right.</i>

26
00:01:32.509 --> 00:01:34.261
- I love you.
- <i>Love you.</i>

27
00:01:35.345 --> 00:01:36.929
- How's she doing?
- You know Gaby.

28
00:01:36.930 --> 00:01:38.890
She's stronger than all of us.

29
00:01:38.891 --> 00:01:40.641
I don't know. I'm pretty strong.

30
00:01:40.642 --> 00:01:43.060
Oh. please. Your heart barely works.

31
00:01:43.061 --> 00:01:45.688
I had to help you off the toilet
this morning.

32
00:01:45.689 --> 00:01:47.607
Well. that's true. I got winded wiping.

33
00:01:47.608 --> 00:01:49.108
- Brian.
- Yeah.

34
00:01:49.109 --> 00:01:51.694
Why did you bring Sutton here today?

35
00:01:51.695 --> 00:01:53.404
It's my nanny day.
I was going to your house.

36
00:01:53.405 --> 00:01:55.489
No reason.
Trying to make your life easier.

37
00:01:55.490 --> 00:01:58.201
Just. you know. me being a good person.

38
00:01:58.202 --> 00:02:00.119
- None of that tracks.
- He's the worst.

39
00:02:00.120 --> 00:02:02.580
But who cares. I just want to eat you up.

40
00:02:02.581 --> 00:02:04.874
- Yeah.
- Wish she'd do that to me.

41
00:02:04.875 --> 00:02:07.752
Lately there's been
no skin-to-skin contact.

42
00:02:07.753 --> 00:02:08.835
if you know what I mean.

43
00:02:08.836 --> 00:02:10.796
Yes. sadly I do know what you mean.

44
00:02:10.797 --> 00:02:13.633
The doctor said you can't have sex
for eight weeks.

45
00:02:13.634 --> 00:02:17.220
"Six to eight". okay?
And I've done the math.

46
00:02:17.221 --> 00:02:20.765
You either owe me 16 you-on-the-bottoms
or four you-on-the-tops.

47
00:02:20.766 --> 00:02:22.975
I am never getting married.

48
00:02:22.976 --> 00:02:26.395
Look at your little Jordans. I love them.

49
00:02:26.396 --> 00:02:28.272
- Everyone's been so supportive…
- Look at these.

50
00:02:28.273 --> 00:02:30.149
…of Matthew's sneaker hustle.

51
00:02:30.150 --> 00:02:32.527
- Thank you guys so much.
- Yes. absolutely.

52
00:02:32.528 --> 00:02:34.570
Are you kidding? I love my new sneakers.

53
00:02:34.571 --> 00:02:36.531
I've been getting hit on so much.

54
00:02:36.532 --> 00:02:39.617
This woman at the coffee shop
would not stop staring at me.

55
00:02:39.618 --> 00:02:41.118
I think that's because
you stole her coffee.

56
00:02:41.119 --> 00:02:43.329
No. Angela is my coffee shop name.

57
00:02:43.330 --> 00:02:45.122
- That's not true.
- It's true.

58
00:02:45.123 --> 00:02:47.458
I was tired of people calling me. "Brain."

59
00:02:47.459 --> 00:02:49.168
You know what.
Angela does suit you better.

60
00:02:49.169 --> 00:02:50.753
Let's call him Angela from now on.

61
00:02:50.754 --> 00:02:52.047
How you like that. Brain?

62
00:02:54.341 --> 00:02:56.802
When I was a kid working at Bellevue.

63
00:02:57.553 --> 00:02:59.262
whenever we lost someone.

64
00:02:59.263 --> 00:03:05.644
my supervisor would gather us together
so that we could process it emotionally.

65
00:03:06.311 --> 00:03:11.524
And then he'd have each of us say
how lucky we were to have each other.

66
00:03:11.525 --> 00:03:13.067
Wow. you'd actually do that?

67
00:03:13.068 --> 00:03:15.695
No. I pretended I had to go take a pee.

68
00:03:15.696 --> 00:03:19.116
but I do remember feeling
like having that community

69
00:03:20.117 --> 00:03:21.410
helped me get through it.

70
00:03:22.744 --> 00:03:24.829
Look. I went over all of your notes.

71
00:03:24.830 --> 00:03:28.166
There's nothing
that you should've done differently.

72
00:03:28.750 --> 00:03:30.084
I know.

73
00:03:30.085 --> 00:03:32.628
I'm sorry.
I know you really cared about her.

74
00:03:32.629 --> 00:03:35.631
Yeah. thanks for that. You encouraged me
to get closer to my patients.

75
00:03:35.632 --> 00:03:38.259
but you didn't warn me how much more
it would hurt if things went south.

76
00:03:38.260 --> 00:03:40.012
I thought that was sort of implied.

77
00:03:40.637 --> 00:03:44.557
Just know that we're aware
how hard this must be.

78
00:03:44.558 --> 00:03:46.560
and that we're here for you.

79
00:03:47.561 --> 00:03:49.145
Well. I'm here for you.

80
00:03:49.146 --> 00:03:51.189
Paul apparently
has a pickup game to get to.

81
00:03:51.190 --> 00:03:54.692
Liz's big. weird son hooked me up.
You're just jealous.

82
00:03:54.693 --> 00:03:58.154
Yes. I've always regretted throwing away
my slime shoes.

83
00:03:58.155 --> 00:04:00.406
All right. gentlemen.
Feels like this meeting is over.

84
00:04:00.407 --> 00:04:03.493
Hey. if you need some time.
I'm happy to cover your patients.

85
00:04:04.077 --> 00:04:06.579
Thanks. but I got it.

86
00:04:06.580 --> 00:04:09.166
- Okay.
- Good. Back on the horse.

87
00:04:10.375 --> 00:04:13.045
That's the way we honor
the people we lose.

88
00:04:14.671 --> 00:04:17.089
You guys are the best. Love you.

89
00:04:18.675 --> 00:04:19.926
What?

90
00:04:19.927 --> 00:04:22.262
I thought of something funny.
but now's not the time.

91
00:04:22.846 --> 00:04:24.805
- Go for it.
- No.

92
00:04:24.806 --> 00:04:26.807
- Come on. I need a laugh.
- Say it. Jimmy.

93
00:04:26.808 --> 00:04:29.602
Okay. You have dead patient face.

94
00:04:29.603 --> 00:04:30.686
- Jesus.
- What?

95
00:04:30.687 --> 00:04:32.021
What the hell is wrong with you?

96
00:04:32.022 --> 00:04:35.066
I was trying to be funny.
I thought that it might lighten the mood.

97
00:04:35.067 --> 00:04:37.110
- Oh. my God.
- 'Cause of dead wife face.

98
00:04:38.904 --> 00:04:40.488
I'm going to hell. aren't I?

99
00:04:40.489 --> 00:04:41.698
Yeah.

100
00:04:42.699 --> 00:04:44.034
See ya there.

101
00:05:15.065 --> 00:05:16.399
God. it is so crazy.

102
00:05:16.400 --> 00:05:19.110
{\an8}It feels like yesterday
I was dropping you off for preschool.

103
00:05:19.111 --> 00:05:20.737
{\an8}and now you're getting ready to graduate.

104
00:05:22.197 --> 00:05:24.407
{\an8}Hey. why didn't you tell me you were voted
"Most Resilient"?

105
00:05:24.408 --> 00:05:26.075
{\an8}Because I hate it.

106
00:05:26.076 --> 00:05:28.786
{\an8}It was me and some kid who lost his finger
to a firework.

107
00:05:28.787 --> 00:05:31.415
{\an8}I got voted "White Michael Jordan."

108
00:05:32.249 --> 00:05:33.542
{\an8}I was really good at basketball.

109
00:05:34.042 --> 00:05:35.460
{\an8}And it was a different time.

110
00:05:38.797 --> 00:05:41.632
{\an8}- Hey. you're back.
- Hey. yeah. hi.

111
00:05:41.633 --> 00:05:43.593
{\an8}- Hey. Yeah.
- Thank you.

112
00:05:43.594 --> 00:05:46.471
{\an8}- Hey.
- Hey. Yeah.

113
00:05:47.222 --> 00:05:50.099
{\an8}I left my. jacket. wallet and keys here

114
00:05:50.100 --> 00:05:52.185
{\an8}the other night
after your dead mom's birthday party.

115
00:05:52.186 --> 00:05:53.895
{\an8}You could just say "Mom."

116
00:05:53.896 --> 00:05:56.689
{\an8}Really?
It's not too soon to be that familiar?

117
00:05:56.690 --> 00:05:59.108
{\an8}Okay. Mom. Cool.

118
00:05:59.109 --> 00:06:00.485
{\an8}Nice.

119
00:06:01.695 --> 00:06:03.237
{\an8}I would've brought you your stuff.

120
00:06:03.238 --> 00:06:05.824
{\an8}Well. I didn't want to seem thirsty.

121
00:06:06.742 --> 00:06:08.910
{\an8}Anyway. that was fun the other night.

122
00:06:08.911 --> 00:06:10.494
{\an8}It's a pretty weird first date. huh?

123
00:06:10.495 --> 00:06:12.121
{\an8}It was such a weird first date.

124
00:06:12.122 --> 00:06:13.789
{\an8}- Yeah.
- That wasn't a date.

125
00:06:13.790 --> 00:06:15.124
{\an8}There were too many people there.

126
00:06:15.125 --> 00:06:18.169
{\an8}An actual date needs to be
just the two of you.

127
00:06:18.170 --> 00:06:20.379
{\an8}Alone. Maybe at a restaurant.

128
00:06:20.380 --> 00:06:22.465
{\an8}I mean. there would be people there too…

129
00:06:22.466 --> 00:06:24.133
{\an8}- …right? The patrons.
- Yes. Uh-huh.

130
00:06:24.134 --> 00:06:25.259
{\an8}Waiters.

131
00:06:25.260 --> 00:06:26.969
{\an8}Maybe a restaurant critic?

132
00:06:26.970 --> 00:06:28.095
{\an8}In disguise.

133
00:06:28.096 --> 00:06:29.972
{\an8}Scribbling madly. In a notebook.

134
00:06:29.973 --> 00:06:32.892
{\an8}- But we are on to him.
- So on to him.

135
00:06:32.893 --> 00:06:33.976
{\an8}Can this be over now?

136
00:06:33.977 --> 00:06:35.645
{\an8}Sure. For now.

137
00:06:35.646 --> 00:06:39.815
{\an8}But. you know. she is right.
We haven't had an official first date.

138
00:06:39.816 --> 00:06:42.402
{\an8}So. how about dinner tomorrow night
at my house?

139
00:06:43.403 --> 00:06:44.404
{\an8}It's a date.

140
00:06:45.030 --> 00:06:46.822
{\an8}Finally.

141
00:06:46.823 --> 00:06:49.033
{\an8}Well. thank you for finding my stuff.

142
00:06:49.034 --> 00:06:51.827
{\an8}Just feel like I keep losing things.

143
00:06:51.828 --> 00:06:53.788
{\an8}- It's really good to see you. Okay.
- Yeah. you too.

144
00:06:53.789 --> 00:06:55.081
{\an8}- Bye. see you tomorrow.
- Yeah.

145
00:06:55.082 --> 00:06:56.416
{\an8}- I'll see you tomorrow. Okay.
- Bye.

146
00:06:58.252 --> 00:06:59.335
{\an8}- Yeah.
- Yeah.

147
00:06:59.336 --> 00:07:00.586
{\an8}She's pretty cool right?

148
00:07:00.587 --> 00:07:02.297
{\an8}Yeah. I do really like her.

149
00:07:03.006 --> 00:07:05.425
{\an8}I kind of think
Mom's making her shit disappear.

150
00:07:07.135 --> 00:07:08.262
Fuck.

151
00:07:09.513 --> 00:07:11.014
{\an8}- Hey.
- Hey.

152
00:07:11.723 --> 00:07:14.183
{\an8}I thought it might cheer you up

153
00:07:14.184 --> 00:07:17.603
{\an8}to take a culinary trip through
your old neighborhood. in Long Beach.

154
00:07:17.604 --> 00:07:21.232
{\an8}I got chili cheese fries
from that very dirty place

155
00:07:21.233 --> 00:07:23.192
{\an8}- across the street from your high school.
- Noice.

156
00:07:23.193 --> 00:07:27.488
{\an8}And a peppermint stick in a pickle from
the gas station near your mom's house…

157
00:07:27.489 --> 00:07:28.823
{\an8}- Hell yeah.
- …which.

158
00:07:28.824 --> 00:07:30.992
{\an8}I can't believe I'm saying this.
is actually pretty bomb.

159
00:07:30.993 --> 00:07:33.620
{\an8}The best part is when you burp
a few days later. you can still taste it.

160
00:07:35.539 --> 00:07:39.250
{\an8}Look. babe. this is really sweet.
but I don't really feel like eating…

161
00:07:39.251 --> 00:07:42.587
{\an8}so… I think I'm on that depression diet…

162
00:07:42.588 --> 00:07:43.797
{\an8}- Right. yeah.
- …for a few days.

163
00:07:44.590 --> 00:07:45.673
Well. how about this?

164
00:07:45.674 --> 00:07:48.009
How about you and I cuddle up on the couch

165
00:07:48.010 --> 00:07:50.678
- and watch some <i>Lord of the Rings</i>?
- Pronounce it right.

166
00:07:50.679 --> 00:07:52.806
- My bad. <i>Lord of the Rangs</i>.
- That's right.

167
00:07:53.765 --> 00:07:57.561
Yeah. Not tonight. babe.

168
00:08:04.234 --> 00:08:07.653
She said no to <i>Lord of the Rangs</i>?
That's her happy place.

169
00:08:07.654 --> 00:08:12.325
I know. Anyway. she's struggling.
so… can you guys keep an eye on her?

170
00:08:12.326 --> 00:08:14.452
- Absolutely.
- I'll deal with this.

171
00:08:14.453 --> 00:08:19.248
I've handled the death of a patient before
and surprisingly. you have not.

172
00:08:19.249 --> 00:08:20.959
I know. it really is amazing. isn't it?

173
00:08:21.919 --> 00:08:23.253
Don't jinx me.

174
00:08:25.923 --> 00:08:28.633
- Thanks for coming by. Derrick.
- Absolutely.

175
00:08:28.634 --> 00:08:30.676
It really is sweet
how much you care about her.

176
00:08:30.677 --> 00:08:33.678
Actually before all this went down.

177
00:08:33.679 --> 00:08:35.890
I was planning to propose.

178
00:08:36.933 --> 00:08:38.017
Nice.

179
00:08:38.018 --> 00:08:41.062
And when were you planning on asking
for my approval?

180
00:08:41.063 --> 00:08:42.731
Asking you for your approval?

181
00:08:43.941 --> 00:08:45.942
Is he serious right now?

182
00:08:45.943 --> 00:08:47.194
I believe he is. yes.

183
00:08:49.780 --> 00:08:52.907
Okay. Well. Paul. if it's okay with you.

184
00:08:52.908 --> 00:08:57.204
I'd love permission
to marry your coworker.

185
00:09:00.040 --> 00:09:01.625
That would make me very happy.

186
00:09:02.334 --> 00:09:04.418
- Hell yeah.
- Wow.

187
00:09:04.419 --> 00:09:07.004
- Wow. wow. wow. wow.
- Right?

188
00:09:07.005 --> 00:09:09.258
Sorry. I think
I'm just in an emotional place.

189
00:09:10.801 --> 00:09:12.301
I have a first date tonight.

190
00:09:12.302 --> 00:09:14.011
Made this about himself real quick.

191
00:09:14.012 --> 00:09:15.764
He always does.

192
00:09:16.348 --> 00:09:18.975
It was so nice of you to tidy up. Ava.

193
00:09:18.976 --> 00:09:22.103
And you did laundry too? Wow.

194
00:09:22.104 --> 00:09:26.065
How fun that my perfectly-fitting
blended fabric T-shirts

195
00:09:26.066 --> 00:09:27.943
got to tumble with your cotton separates.

196
00:09:28.569 --> 00:09:31.404
Just my way of saying thank you
for letting me crash here

197
00:09:31.405 --> 00:09:33.948
- for the last few weeks.
- Come on. We are happy to help.

198
00:09:33.949 --> 00:09:37.869
And I know it's been taking me a while
to find a new job. and a new place.

199
00:09:37.870 --> 00:09:40.997
so. until then. I will do
all the housework around here.

200
00:09:40.998 --> 00:09:43.374
- Then stay as long as you want.
- Our home is your home.

201
00:09:43.375 --> 00:09:44.417
Hello?

202
00:09:44.418 --> 00:09:46.210
- Run.
- You need to leave right now.

203
00:09:46.211 --> 00:09:47.545
Angela? Are you decent?

204
00:09:47.546 --> 00:09:49.297
Nope! We just had sex!

205
00:09:49.298 --> 00:09:51.424
- Here. go. stall her.
- What?

206
00:09:51.425 --> 00:09:53.384
- Come on. Gotta go.
- Liz.

207
00:09:53.385 --> 00:09:55.386
What? Why? Why do I have to go?
Liz likes me.

208
00:09:55.387 --> 00:09:58.139
Yeah. no. she does. She really likes you.
but she also has a lot of opinions.

209
00:09:58.140 --> 00:09:59.974
so she's gonna have thoughts
about you living here.

210
00:09:59.975 --> 00:10:02.643
You know. like. "But for how long?"
and "What does this mean?"

211
00:10:02.644 --> 00:10:04.896
and "Isn't it an unhealthy dynamic
for the birth mother

212
00:10:04.897 --> 00:10:06.606
to be living with the adoptive parents?"

213
00:10:06.607 --> 00:10:09.317
You know. stupid shit like that.
This door. Okay.

214
00:10:09.318 --> 00:10:10.401
Down.

215
00:10:10.402 --> 00:10:13.487
I don't want to hear your life story.
Charlie. Nobody cares.

216
00:10:13.488 --> 00:10:15.698
- I just want to see my baby.
- Liz.

217
00:10:15.699 --> 00:10:18.743
Hey. Liz. What's up. girl?

218
00:10:18.744 --> 00:10:20.119
I have noticed

219
00:10:20.120 --> 00:10:22.914
that you weren't keeping up
with Sutton's moisturizing routine.

220
00:10:22.915 --> 00:10:27.502
so I brought a cream from Europe
that's banned here

221
00:10:27.503 --> 00:10:28.837
but will keep her smooth forever.

222
00:10:29.505 --> 00:10:30.630
May I try?

223
00:10:30.631 --> 00:10:32.341
I think it's a little late for you.

224
00:10:33.634 --> 00:10:34.843
Okay.

225
00:10:36.094 --> 00:10:37.178
What do you think?

226
00:10:37.179 --> 00:10:39.430
Someone came to play.

227
00:10:39.431 --> 00:10:41.099
Come on. give us a spin.

228
00:10:42.684 --> 00:10:45.311
- Yeah! Nice.
- Uh-huh.

229
00:10:45.312 --> 00:10:46.687
I'm good?

230
00:10:46.688 --> 00:10:47.898
You look like a princess.

231
00:10:48.398 --> 00:10:50.191
I sort of feel like one.

232
00:10:50.192 --> 00:10:52.568
- You're glowing.
- I think that might be panic sweat.

233
00:10:52.569 --> 00:10:54.279
You're 'scited.

234
00:10:55.197 --> 00:10:56.531
Scared and excited.

235
00:10:56.532 --> 00:10:58.783
I learned it in kindergarten.
It really stuck with me.

236
00:10:58.784 --> 00:11:00.910
Just. there's been
a lot of buildup. you know?

237
00:11:00.911 --> 00:11:04.372
A lot of missed chances.
I just really want it to go well.

238
00:11:04.373 --> 00:11:07.751
I know it's been a while.
so you just have to remember.

239
00:11:08.418 --> 00:11:10.170
the first stop on her train…

240
00:11:11.672 --> 00:11:13.214
it's gotta be downtown.

241
00:11:13.215 --> 00:11:14.715
I hate horny Derek.

242
00:11:14.716 --> 00:11:15.842
I black it out.

243
00:11:15.843 --> 00:11:17.844
- I mean. he ain't wrong.
- He ain't wrong.

244
00:11:17.845 --> 00:11:19.513
All right. well…

245
00:11:21.348 --> 00:11:22.431
Wish me luck.

246
00:11:22.432 --> 00:11:24.685
I'm gonna give you the same advice
you gave me on my first date.

247
00:11:25.769 --> 00:11:27.437
Be yourself. have fun.

248
00:11:27.938 --> 00:11:29.648
and you can't put
the toothpaste back in the tube.

249
00:11:30.816 --> 00:11:32.483
I think the toothpaste was my virginity.

250
00:11:32.484 --> 00:11:34.819
- Yeah. we got it.
- I had no idea.

251
00:11:34.820 --> 00:11:35.988
Here goes nothing.

252
00:11:37.739 --> 00:11:39.283
Hey.

253
00:11:40.158 --> 00:11:41.577
You've got this.

254
00:11:42.202 --> 00:11:43.245
Thanks. kiddo.

255
00:11:47.040 --> 00:11:49.751
I gave my toothpaste to my math tutor.

256
00:11:51.962 --> 00:11:53.755
Yeah. I think it went really well.

257
00:11:54.464 --> 00:11:57.133
Even though nobody
at the restaurant told me

258
00:11:57.134 --> 00:11:59.635
I'd be interviewing with Dre Thibodeaux.

259
00:11:59.636 --> 00:12:01.387
The Dre Thibodeaux?

260
00:12:01.388 --> 00:12:03.264
- Stop doing that.
- Never.

261
00:12:03.265 --> 00:12:04.266
Anyway.

262
00:12:05.100 --> 00:12:07.311
There's a lot of people up
for this job and…

263
00:12:07.978 --> 00:12:09.729
it's just real cool to be in the mix.

264
00:12:09.730 --> 00:12:12.941
Fuck the mix. Sky's the limit for you.
kid. you just got to believe it.

265
00:12:14.151 --> 00:12:15.152
Oh. shit.

266
00:12:15.903 --> 00:12:17.028
Almost time for group.

267
00:12:17.029 --> 00:12:19.572
- I gotta get going.
- Hey.

268
00:12:19.573 --> 00:12:22.033
Gaby helps run the veterans group. right?

269
00:12:22.034 --> 00:12:23.702
- Yeah.
- Do me a favor.

270
00:12:24.369 --> 00:12:25.453
Ask me to come.

271
00:12:25.454 --> 00:12:28.289
Wouldn't it be kinda weird.
since you're not a vet?

272
00:12:28.290 --> 00:12:29.917
I'd love to.

273
00:12:31.877 --> 00:12:33.837
All right. everybody!
Time to circle up. let's go.

274
00:12:35.088 --> 00:12:36.297
Paul?

275
00:12:36.298 --> 00:12:37.341
What are you doing here?

276
00:12:37.925 --> 00:12:40.426
That would be me. I asked him to come.

277
00:12:40.427 --> 00:12:41.970
Why?

278
00:12:43.388 --> 00:12:44.389
'Cause he told me to.

279
00:12:45.432 --> 00:12:46.683
Smooth.

280
00:12:47.267 --> 00:12:51.854
I think what you're doing is great.
so I thought I'd drop by and check it out.

281
00:12:51.855 --> 00:12:52.939
- Really?
- Yeah.

282
00:12:52.940 --> 00:12:55.107
Then why haven't you said anything.
not even once?

283
00:12:55.108 --> 00:12:56.568
I'm shy.

284
00:12:57.402 --> 00:13:00.197
All right. well. sit your ass down.
and stay shy.

285
00:13:01.907 --> 00:13:04.659
Hey. How you… How you doing?

286
00:13:04.660 --> 00:13:07.662
Fellow vet. huh?
Guessing Revolutionary War.

287
00:13:07.663 --> 00:13:09.163
Did you know Paul Revere?

288
00:13:09.164 --> 00:13:11.583
No. But I knew your mama.

289
00:13:13.418 --> 00:13:14.962
This is gonna be fun.

290
00:13:16.880 --> 00:13:18.422
Guys?

291
00:13:18.423 --> 00:13:21.844
Am I crazy. or is that Ava's purse?

292
00:13:22.761 --> 00:13:23.928
She must have forgotten it.

293
00:13:23.929 --> 00:13:25.847
Yeah. Liz. relax.
it's not like she lives here.

294
00:13:25.848 --> 00:13:26.931
Why would you say that?

295
00:13:26.932 --> 00:13:28.808
So she does live here?

296
00:13:28.809 --> 00:13:30.268
No.

297
00:13:30.269 --> 00:13:31.854
So. whose thong is this?

298
00:13:32.980 --> 00:13:33.981
Mine.

299
00:13:34.606 --> 00:13:35.731
It's yours?

300
00:13:35.732 --> 00:13:36.941
Yeah. I love a thong.

301
00:13:36.942 --> 00:13:39.485
- 'Cause they're so comfy?
- That's right.

302
00:13:39.486 --> 00:13:40.863
Okay. Put it on.

303
00:13:42.739 --> 00:13:44.073
Why wouldn't I?

304
00:13:44.074 --> 00:13:47.994
I'm just gonna sit here
and enjoy the show.

305
00:13:47.995 --> 00:13:50.037
- Can't wait.
- Don't do this.

306
00:13:50.038 --> 00:13:51.039
Well. I'm doing it.

307
00:13:54.751 --> 00:13:56.919
You realize
this isn't gonna cover everything?

308
00:13:56.920 --> 00:13:58.714
I feel like there's a chance it might.

309
00:13:59.631 --> 00:14:02.592
Well. here we go.

310
00:14:02.593 --> 00:14:04.177
- Ava is staying here.
- Charlie!

311
00:14:04.178 --> 00:14:06.554
- What was your plan?
- To put on this thong.

312
00:14:06.555 --> 00:14:08.764
and. if we're being real.
probably enjoy wearing it.

313
00:14:08.765 --> 00:14:11.267
Ava is living with you?

314
00:14:11.268 --> 00:14:14.854
She lost her waitressing job
and she couldn't afford to pay rent.

315
00:14:14.855 --> 00:14:16.939
And her parents
have practically disowned her.

316
00:14:16.940 --> 00:14:18.608
so she couldn't move back home.

317
00:14:18.609 --> 00:14:22.778
I told you that letting Ava
into your lives was a slippery slope.

318
00:14:22.779 --> 00:14:26.825
And you open the door a crack
and now there's a thong up in it.

319
00:14:27.409 --> 00:14:29.202
What if something bad
had happened to her. Liz?

320
00:14:29.203 --> 00:14:31.579
What if she'd been
forced out onto the street

321
00:14:31.580 --> 00:14:34.332
and had to get a sugar daddy

322
00:14:34.333 --> 00:14:38.419
or marry some old. rich man
that she didn't really love?

323
00:14:38.420 --> 00:14:41.547
Oh. my God. What am I saying?
It's like I'm describing my perfect life.

324
00:14:41.548 --> 00:14:47.220
I get it. Letting Ava move in…
was a compassionate thing to do.

325
00:14:47.221 --> 00:14:48.888
Yes.

326
00:14:48.889 --> 00:14:51.516
Thank you. I knew you'd understand.

327
00:14:51.517 --> 00:14:53.226
It's just temporary.

328
00:14:53.227 --> 00:14:55.937
She's really trying to find a job.

329
00:14:55.938 --> 00:14:57.647
Wait. wait.

330
00:14:57.648 --> 00:15:02.109
You guys think that someone
as pretty as Ava can't find a job?

331
00:15:02.110 --> 00:15:07.324
She couldn't just ditch her bra
and be selling tequila shots somewhere?

332
00:15:08.951 --> 00:15:11.452
Wow. Liz. I hope for Sutton's sake

333
00:15:11.453 --> 00:15:15.582
that our society is not as shallow
as you seem to think it is.

334
00:15:20.754 --> 00:15:21.755
Is this yours?

335
00:15:26.009 --> 00:15:27.426
Well. I don't see her.

336
00:15:27.427 --> 00:15:28.470
And…

337
00:15:31.390 --> 00:15:33.599
{\an8}I hate it when you're right.

338
00:15:33.600 --> 00:15:35.477
{\an8}I'm getting bored of it myself.

339
00:15:38.146 --> 00:15:39.147
Hi.

340
00:15:39.940 --> 00:15:41.023
You look great.

341
00:15:41.024 --> 00:15:42.400
Thanks.

342
00:15:42.401 --> 00:15:46.737
Cheers. But right up-front.
you're not getting to second base.

343
00:15:46.738 --> 00:15:49.031
I'm wearing my house bra.

344
00:15:49.032 --> 00:15:50.741
Oh. yeah. I was married. I know the one.

345
00:15:50.742 --> 00:15:52.368
No underwire.

346
00:15:52.369 --> 00:15:55.121
Yeah. you get it. Sort of like a sack
you throw your boobs in.

347
00:15:55.122 --> 00:15:57.415
- Yeah. that's the one.
- So heads-up.

348
00:15:57.416 --> 00:16:00.376
My ex-husband came
to pick up my son for the night.

349
00:16:00.377 --> 00:16:01.753
but they haven't left yet.

350
00:16:02.379 --> 00:16:05.047
I was actually sort of hoping
I would meet your ex tonight.

351
00:16:05.048 --> 00:16:06.883
- Really?
- No. not at all.

352
00:16:06.884 --> 00:16:08.468
Right. That's insane.

353
00:16:10.304 --> 00:16:11.430
Okay.

354
00:16:12.848 --> 00:16:16.517
Jimmy. this is my son. Tate.
And this is Nick.

355
00:16:16.518 --> 00:16:18.561
- This is my friend. Jimmy.
- Hey. hey.

356
00:16:18.562 --> 00:16:20.980
- Hey. Nice to meet you.
- Sofi tells me you're a therapist.

357
00:16:20.981 --> 00:16:23.024
- I am.
- I used to think about doing that.

358
00:16:23.025 --> 00:16:26.402
Still could. You know. just takes.
like. eight years of grad school.

359
00:16:26.403 --> 00:16:29.406
That was the rub. Only took me one year
to learn poolscape design.

360
00:16:30.157 --> 00:16:32.742
I specialize in nature-based water slides.

361
00:16:32.743 --> 00:16:35.537
Very cool. Water attractions
really aren't my thing.

362
00:16:36.038 --> 00:16:38.080
I almost drowned once in a lazy river.

363
00:16:38.081 --> 00:16:39.750
- As a kid?
- No.

364
00:16:40.334 --> 00:16:42.376
Okay. Tate. don't be rude.
can you say hi to Jimmy?

365
00:16:42.377 --> 00:16:44.171
- 'Sup?
- Nailed it.

366
00:16:44.671 --> 00:16:48.132
Okay. let's get going.
Why did we start playing a video game?

367
00:16:48.133 --> 00:16:49.217
That was my fault.

368
00:16:49.218 --> 00:16:51.177
I promised him if he got an A
on his spelling test.

369
00:16:51.178 --> 00:16:53.804
then he could do a round
of <i>Diablo Dungeons</i>.

370
00:16:53.805 --> 00:16:54.847
Okay.

371
00:16:54.848 --> 00:16:56.224
We don't do screens in my house.

372
00:16:56.225 --> 00:16:57.392
Screens suck.

373
00:16:58.435 --> 00:17:00.437
Now I'm siding against you
for absolutely no reason.

374
00:17:01.730 --> 00:17:04.022
We could always. like. go out instead.
if you want.

375
00:17:04.023 --> 00:17:07.069
But I made coq au vin.
Mostly 'cause I like saying it.

376
00:17:07.694 --> 00:17:09.111
You don't have to leave.

377
00:17:09.112 --> 00:17:10.905
As soon as he dies. then we'll take off.

378
00:17:10.906 --> 00:17:12.490
He's never gonna get past Drex.

379
00:17:12.491 --> 00:17:15.159
Great. let's stick with the coq au vin.

380
00:17:15.160 --> 00:17:17.912
- <i>You just beat Drex.</i>
- Oh. my God!

381
00:17:17.913 --> 00:17:19.498
No way! He got past Drex!

382
00:17:20.165 --> 00:17:22.251
<i>Level up
Level. level. level up!</i>

383
00:17:22.876 --> 00:17:24.876
<i>Level up. level. level. level up!</i>

384
00:17:24.877 --> 00:17:26.629
- I'm sorry.
- No. It's cool.

385
00:17:26.630 --> 00:17:28.590
I think this is all really cool.

386
00:17:29.883 --> 00:17:33.219
All right. since you're new here.
introduce yourself by saying your name.

387
00:17:33.220 --> 00:17:35.639
age. and your favorite one hit wonder band
from the '90s.

388
00:17:36.223 --> 00:17:39.767
Paul. 74. Marky Mark and the Funky Bunch.

389
00:17:39.768 --> 00:17:41.811
The fuck is a Funky Bunch?

390
00:17:41.812 --> 00:17:44.063
- I'll tell you later.
- All right.

391
00:17:44.064 --> 00:17:47.108
I want to begin by addressing
the elephant in the room

392
00:17:47.109 --> 00:17:48.610
of Maya's untimely passing.

393
00:17:49.278 --> 00:17:53.281
Many of you got to know Maya.
when she started coming here for MMA.

394
00:17:53.282 --> 00:17:55.117
I'm sure you all have feelings about it.

395
00:17:56.410 --> 00:17:57.411
I'll start.

396
00:17:59.413 --> 00:18:00.497
This sucks.

397
00:18:01.582 --> 00:18:03.667
She was definitely going
through some shit.

398
00:18:04.960 --> 00:18:06.879
But she smiled when she was here.

399
00:18:08.922 --> 00:18:10.048
And she had a great smile.

400
00:18:11.133 --> 00:18:15.178
It's weird that the last time I saw her.
I was punching her in the face.

401
00:18:15.179 --> 00:18:17.054
- Dude.
- Still shook up.

402
00:18:17.055 --> 00:18:19.432
Sometimes when we lose
even an acquaintance.

403
00:18:19.433 --> 00:18:21.517
it can stir up the pain of past losses.

404
00:18:21.518 --> 00:18:22.852
Isn't that right. Paul?

405
00:18:22.853 --> 00:18:26.273
Yeah. it's called "cumulative grief."

406
00:18:27.316 --> 00:18:30.152
And just like in MMA.
you gotta keep your guard up.

407
00:18:30.861 --> 00:18:33.238
Even when you think you're okay.

408
00:18:33.864 --> 00:18:39.036
the sadness can sneak up on you
and kick your ass.

409
00:18:39.703 --> 00:18:40.786
And that's why

410
00:18:40.787 --> 00:18:43.332
it's important to let your friends
show up for you.

411
00:18:43.916 --> 00:18:46.502
Even your shy ones who bullshit
about why they're really here.

412
00:18:47.002 --> 00:18:48.294
What's happening?

413
00:18:48.295 --> 00:18:50.172
They talking about us.
but really about them.

414
00:18:52.341 --> 00:18:54.676
I busted that dead chicks lip. bro.

415
00:18:55.219 --> 00:18:56.719
I know. man.

416
00:18:56.720 --> 00:18:57.929
You good.

417
00:18:57.930 --> 00:19:00.681
- Plus. she kicked your ass.
- She sure did.

418
00:19:00.682 --> 00:19:01.767
I know.

419
00:19:04.561 --> 00:19:06.271
Hi. I'm Ava--

420
00:19:07.940 --> 00:19:09.232
Shit.

421
00:19:09.233 --> 00:19:11.068
Can you sit with us for a minute?

422
00:19:11.777 --> 00:19:15.197
Just let me tell the manager. She's cool.

423
00:19:16.156 --> 00:19:18.824
That's great that she's cool.

424
00:19:18.825 --> 00:19:21.244
- What are you doing?
- I don't know.

425
00:19:21.245 --> 00:19:24.163
I don't like ambushing her like this.
Makes it seem like I don't trust her.

426
00:19:24.164 --> 00:19:25.414
Because you don't trust her.

427
00:19:25.415 --> 00:19:26.833
That's because you made me not trust her.

428
00:19:26.834 --> 00:19:28.251
- That's not true.
- Yes. it is true.

429
00:19:28.252 --> 00:19:29.418
It's totally true. It's true.

430
00:19:29.419 --> 00:19:32.839
Look. I have to have
a functional relationship with Ava

431
00:19:32.840 --> 00:19:34.215
for the rest of my life.

432
00:19:34.216 --> 00:19:35.800
- I'm leaving.
- Oh. stop. No. wait.

433
00:19:35.801 --> 00:19:37.468
We have to confront her.

434
00:19:37.469 --> 00:19:38.719
You do whatever you want.

435
00:19:38.720 --> 00:19:42.473
I'm just gonna love her
and bravely run away.

436
00:19:42.474 --> 00:19:45.268
- Brian.
- Hey. hey. Bye. Ava.

437
00:19:45.269 --> 00:19:47.980
- I'll see you at home.
- Bye.

438
00:19:48.856 --> 00:19:50.148
No.

439
00:19:51.149 --> 00:19:52.484
Okay.

440
00:19:55.445 --> 00:19:58.865
Look. I only planned to stay
with Brian and Charlie a little while.

441
00:19:58.866 --> 00:20:00.409
Okay. so what happened?

442
00:20:01.159 --> 00:20:05.621
Turns out. living with them is great.
Things have been so hard with my parents.

443
00:20:05.622 --> 00:20:10.543
Anyway. I got this job last week.
but I just wasn't ready to go.

444
00:20:10.544 --> 00:20:12.795
Ava. you deserve to have a great life.

445
00:20:12.796 --> 00:20:15.548
but you've gotta give them their space.

446
00:20:15.549 --> 00:20:18.676
By being this involved in their family.

447
00:20:18.677 --> 00:20:21.929
you're not allowing them the chance
to build theirs.

448
00:20:21.930 --> 00:20:25.350
Okay. But how are you any different?

449
00:20:26.643 --> 00:20:28.769
You walk into their house
whenever you want

450
00:20:28.770 --> 00:20:30.438
and you call their baby your baby.

451
00:20:30.439 --> 00:20:31.731
Sutton likes when I do that.

452
00:20:31.732 --> 00:20:35.526
Liz. you tracked me down to talk to me
about what should go on

453
00:20:35.527 --> 00:20:39.655
in Brian's house without Brian.
in an Olive Garden.

454
00:20:39.656 --> 00:20:42.658
A restaurant I am near positive
you've never been to in your life.

455
00:20:42.659 --> 00:20:45.119
I come here all the time.

456
00:20:45.120 --> 00:20:47.663
I love their carb wands.

457
00:20:47.664 --> 00:20:52.127
Those are called "breadsticks."
And I know you want to try one.

458
00:21:00.802 --> 00:21:01.886
What now?

459
00:21:01.887 --> 00:21:06.265
I don't know.
But I definitely need more of these.

460
00:21:06.266 --> 00:21:07.267
On it.

461
00:21:08.060 --> 00:21:11.062
Maybe some fried ravioli? I mean…

462
00:21:11.063 --> 00:21:13.815
This is. like. surprisingly delicious.

463
00:21:14.650 --> 00:21:15.858
Wish I hadn't said surprisingly.

464
00:21:15.859 --> 00:21:16.984
It's okay.

465
00:21:16.985 --> 00:21:20.363
I was gonna say
I got this recipe from a trip to Paris.

466
00:21:20.364 --> 00:21:23.658
but it's actually from Guy Fieri.

467
00:21:23.659 --> 00:21:26.285
The only time I was in Paris.

468
00:21:26.286 --> 00:21:28.996
I was dating this woman. and we did

469
00:21:28.997 --> 00:21:31.582
- that whole lock-on-a-bridge thing.
- Oh. yeah.

470
00:21:31.583 --> 00:21:33.417
It's funny I can't even
remember her name right now.

471
00:21:33.418 --> 00:21:34.544
Come on. Yes. you do.

472
00:21:34.545 --> 00:21:36.796
Yes. I do. I just hate
that it's not a pretty name.

473
00:21:36.797 --> 00:21:38.464
Bernice.

474
00:21:38.465 --> 00:21:40.299
You dated a Bernie.

475
00:21:40.300 --> 00:21:41.467
I dated a Bernie.

476
00:21:41.468 --> 00:21:42.677
- Wow.
- Yeah.

477
00:21:42.678 --> 00:21:44.888
Last person I dated before…

478
00:21:45.931 --> 00:21:46.932
Tia.

479
00:21:47.850 --> 00:21:49.976
Yeah. Sorry.
She keeps coming up. doesn't she?

480
00:21:49.977 --> 00:21:51.061
No. it's okay.

481
00:21:51.728 --> 00:21:54.815
It's really special how much you miss her.

482
00:21:56.066 --> 00:22:00.279
Seriously. it feels like
that kind of love is once in a lifetime.

483
00:22:01.280 --> 00:22:02.406
Maybe.

484
00:22:03.615 --> 00:22:04.992
Sure hope not. though.

485
00:22:09.663 --> 00:22:11.289
Grabbing the toolbox.

486
00:22:11.290 --> 00:22:13.791
Tate made another level. so he's on fire.

487
00:22:13.792 --> 00:22:15.543
- Cool.
- Fuckin' Drex.

488
00:22:15.544 --> 00:22:18.296
I'm gonna go fix the back window screen.
Someone could break in.

489
00:22:18.297 --> 00:22:21.257
I'm not sure a screen
is gonna stop a burglar.

490
00:22:21.258 --> 00:22:22.341
He's remarried.

491
00:22:22.342 --> 00:22:24.886
He has his own place.
but he still struts around here

492
00:22:24.887 --> 00:22:26.053
like he owns it.

493
00:22:26.054 --> 00:22:28.014
You're the one that's always calling me
to come fix stuff.

494
00:22:28.015 --> 00:22:30.850
Because you're always showing up
unannounced.

495
00:22:30.851 --> 00:22:33.227
He insists on having a key.

496
00:22:33.228 --> 00:22:35.689
'Cause she insists
on having primary custody.

497
00:22:36.815 --> 00:22:38.566
- Okay. I'm sorry.
- Okay.

498
00:22:38.567 --> 00:22:41.819
- Yep.
- We haven't really nailed the transition

499
00:22:41.820 --> 00:22:43.362
to respectful co-parenting.

500
00:22:43.363 --> 00:22:46.574
Well. it's nothing a little counseling
wouldn't nip in the bud.

501
00:22:46.575 --> 00:22:50.286
Yes. that is what I keep saying.
but one of us is being a bitch about it.

502
00:22:50.287 --> 00:22:52.789
- Come on.
- Calm down. I didn't say who.

503
00:22:53.624 --> 00:22:54.833
It's him.

504
00:22:56.293 --> 00:23:00.047
If only I knew a good therapist.

505
00:23:00.631 --> 00:23:03.799
- Absolutely not.
- You're a bad therapist?

506
00:23:03.800 --> 00:23:05.176
No. I'm awesome.

507
00:23:05.177 --> 00:23:07.678
But it would be wildly inappropriate. so…

508
00:23:07.679 --> 00:23:10.431
Come on. I'm here. he's here.

509
00:23:10.432 --> 00:23:12.725
Can't you just do that thing
that you told me about

510
00:23:12.726 --> 00:23:14.810
where you go. I don't know. rogue?

511
00:23:14.811 --> 00:23:17.063
"Jimmying." Thought that
would have stuck with you.

512
00:23:17.064 --> 00:23:18.189
I mean it's just my name.

513
00:23:18.190 --> 00:23:19.942
- Jimmying then?
- Yeah.

514
00:23:20.484 --> 00:23:23.611
No. Sorry.
I'm just gonna enjoy coq au vin.

515
00:23:23.612 --> 00:23:26.656
See. she always does this.

516
00:23:26.657 --> 00:23:28.533
She's always putting people on the spot.

517
00:23:28.534 --> 00:23:30.493
- That's me putting you on the spot?
- Yeah.

518
00:23:30.494 --> 00:23:33.412
Because I'm trying to actually confront
you about something that happened.

519
00:23:33.413 --> 00:23:37.333
Listen. I wanna get back to our date.
so I'm just gonna cut right to it.

520
00:23:37.334 --> 00:23:41.671
Nick. I am sensing
that you have unresolved attachment.

521
00:23:41.672 --> 00:23:43.339
So unresolved.

522
00:23:43.340 --> 00:23:44.966
- Not super helpful.
- Okay.

523
00:23:44.967 --> 00:23:46.884
Your frequent presence
around Sofi's house.

524
00:23:46.885 --> 00:23:50.805
it probably isn't about fixing stuff.
or co-parenting.

525
00:23:50.806 --> 00:23:53.766
It's about easing your guilt
over blowing up your marriage.

526
00:23:53.767 --> 00:23:56.060
You're just taking her side
'cause you want to sleep with her.

527
00:23:56.061 --> 00:23:58.772
Sofi. You also have unresolved attachment.

528
00:24:00.357 --> 00:24:01.858
Maybe he doesn't want to sleep with you.

529
00:24:01.859 --> 00:24:04.819
- Yes. he does.
- Suck it.

530
00:24:04.820 --> 00:24:06.737
I think you tolerate his dysfunction

531
00:24:06.738 --> 00:24:09.907
because it's easier for you to default
to your old dynamic.

532
00:24:09.908 --> 00:24:12.202
which includes having a built-in handyman.

533
00:24:12.870 --> 00:24:14.745
than it is to learn how to set boundaries.

534
00:24:14.746 --> 00:24:16.330
Look. you can't keep blaming Nick

535
00:24:16.331 --> 00:24:19.418
until you clearly define
what your boundaries are.

536
00:24:23.338 --> 00:24:24.756
I want my house key back.

537
00:24:34.266 --> 00:24:36.058
Thank you for seeing us today.

538
00:24:36.059 --> 00:24:38.144
I'm always available
for emergency sessions.

539
00:24:38.145 --> 00:24:40.730
Although. this one's obviously
a little different

540
00:24:40.731 --> 00:24:43.024
than that time Mark sent money
to that Instagram model.

541
00:24:43.025 --> 00:24:45.276
She needed supplies for her class.

542
00:24:45.277 --> 00:24:47.695
She taught tai chi in the park.

543
00:24:47.696 --> 00:24:48.697
All right.

544
00:24:50.490 --> 00:24:52.575
I know how much Maya meant
to the both of you.

545
00:24:52.576 --> 00:24:54.369
We're just trying to make sense of it.

546
00:24:56.121 --> 00:24:57.872
I heard she had drugs in her system

547
00:24:57.873 --> 00:25:02.294
and I didn't know
she had an issue with that. Did you?

548
00:25:02.920 --> 00:25:04.420
I can't really speak to specifics

549
00:25:04.421 --> 00:25:06.590
because I still have
to protect Maya's privacy.

550
00:25:07.257 --> 00:25:09.550
but I do have a lot
of experience with addiction.

551
00:25:09.551 --> 00:25:12.261
and unfortunately. things like this
can and do happen

552
00:25:12.262 --> 00:25:13.305
to people who self-medicate.

553
00:25:13.889 --> 00:25:17.058
We talked to her aunt at the funeral

554
00:25:17.059 --> 00:25:21.062
and she told us
that Maya's mom had a drug problem too

555
00:25:21.063 --> 00:25:23.857
and abandoned her when she was ten.

556
00:25:25.108 --> 00:25:26.442
You didn't know that?

557
00:25:26.443 --> 00:25:28.694
Okay. Maya and I were
just starting our work together.

558
00:25:28.695 --> 00:25:31.781
and I am sure
that if I had just a little more time…

559
00:25:31.782 --> 00:25:33.783
- If you had more time?
- …she'd have told me about that.

560
00:25:33.784 --> 00:25:37.203
Maya was obviously in trouble.
Aren't you supposed to see that?

561
00:25:37.204 --> 00:25:39.997
What did you talk about in here?

562
00:25:39.998 --> 00:25:43.751
I understand that you guys
are feeling angry and confused

563
00:25:43.752 --> 00:25:45.211
and it is okay to take it out on me.

564
00:25:45.212 --> 00:25:47.713
It just feels a little weird

565
00:25:47.714 --> 00:25:50.551
that we seem to know more about this
than you do.

566
00:25:52.511 --> 00:25:54.137
Yeah. okay…

567
00:25:54.805 --> 00:25:58.182
Guys. given what's happened.
I do think. you know. it's good for me

568
00:25:58.183 --> 00:26:01.978
to acknowledge that there may
be a loss of trust here.

569
00:26:01.979 --> 00:26:04.480
And as much as I value and care
about you guys.

570
00:26:04.481 --> 00:26:08.651
I am obligated to ask if you guys
would feel more comfortable

571
00:26:08.652 --> 00:26:10.821
seeing someone else moving forward?

572
00:26:16.410 --> 00:26:17.411
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

573
00:26:19.830 --> 00:26:23.875
Wow. See that? You finally did it.
You agreed on something.

574
00:26:23.876 --> 00:26:27.838
Yeah. I did that. Yay.

575
00:26:29.298 --> 00:26:30.923
What the hell. Liz?

576
00:26:30.924 --> 00:26:33.134
Ava just texted us
that she's moving in with a friend.

577
00:26:33.135 --> 00:26:34.427
You totally overstepped here.

578
00:26:34.428 --> 00:26:36.345
Yep. And it's all your fault.

579
00:26:36.346 --> 00:26:39.432
Our fault? How come
we're the ones in trouble right now?

580
00:26:39.433 --> 00:26:44.270
Because you let me take over.
You let me bulldoze you at every turn.

581
00:26:44.271 --> 00:26:46.480
- Liz--
- Not now. Charlie. I'm talking.

582
00:26:46.481 --> 00:26:48.941
- Sorry.
- See? You just did it again.

583
00:26:48.942 --> 00:26:50.194
You have to fire me.

584
00:26:51.069 --> 00:26:52.653
We're not gonna fire you.

585
00:26:52.654 --> 00:26:54.280
You're raising a child.

586
00:26:54.281 --> 00:26:57.491
You have to be in control
of your own home.

587
00:26:57.492 --> 00:26:58.994
- Do it.
- I…

588
00:26:59.661 --> 00:27:02.747
Don't look to him for permission.
you coward. Do it.

589
00:27:02.748 --> 00:27:05.833
- You're fired.
- No. I'm not.

590
00:27:05.834 --> 00:27:08.670
Do you guys know
what the word "assertive" means?

591
00:27:09.421 --> 00:27:10.588
If it helps.

592
00:27:10.589 --> 00:27:14.760
I took Sutton to her first brunch
behind your back.

593
00:27:15.928 --> 00:27:19.472
And I took photos of her
holding my mimosa.

594
00:27:19.473 --> 00:27:24.769
We were saving that to do
as a family. you whore.

595
00:27:24.770 --> 00:27:27.188
- Get her.
- We are sick and tired of you

596
00:27:27.189 --> 00:27:29.065
- acting like you run this house.
- Yeah.

597
00:27:29.066 --> 00:27:31.651
When Sutton should sleep and where.

598
00:27:31.652 --> 00:27:33.486
- how we should feed her…
- Yeah.

599
00:27:33.487 --> 00:27:35.613
…bathe her. burp her.

600
00:27:35.614 --> 00:27:37.323
We are her parents. Liz.

601
00:27:37.324 --> 00:27:38.950
- Us.
- You want a baby? Tough titties.

602
00:27:38.951 --> 00:27:41.118
You're gonna have to wait
for one of those dumb sons of yours

603
00:27:41.119 --> 00:27:42.788
to make you a grandma!

604
00:27:44.581 --> 00:27:46.500
There. You did it.

605
00:27:48.126 --> 00:27:51.129
I'm fired. And it's for the best.

606
00:27:53.549 --> 00:27:55.884
Obviously. Sutton will miss me.

607
00:27:56.718 --> 00:28:02.515
You know. our little nuzzles
and our bath time routine

608
00:28:02.516 --> 00:28:04.350
with the little duckies. and…

609
00:28:04.351 --> 00:28:05.685
Well…

610
00:28:05.686 --> 00:28:08.730
- But it's okay.
- Hey. no. Liz.

611
00:28:09.439 --> 00:28:12.108
We appreciate
everything you've done for us.

612
00:28:12.109 --> 00:28:14.443
We truly never could've gotten to a place

613
00:28:14.444 --> 00:28:17.614
of needing only one full-time nanny
without you.

614
00:28:21.285 --> 00:28:24.620
- Thank you for everything you taught us.
- You're welcome.

615
00:28:24.621 --> 00:28:26.747
Please stay in her life.

616
00:28:26.748 --> 00:28:30.960
I'm still gonna come over whenever I like.

617
00:28:30.961 --> 00:28:33.422
I'm just not gonna babysit
for free anymore.

618
00:28:35.966 --> 00:28:37.134
What have we done?

619
00:28:37.634 --> 00:28:40.429
All right. Bye. buddy.
Good job killing Drex.

620
00:28:43.098 --> 00:28:45.434
I'm not gonna say
that was a great first date.

621
00:28:46.101 --> 00:28:48.144
But there was awesome food.

622
00:28:48.145 --> 00:28:49.478
Interesting conversation.

623
00:28:49.479 --> 00:28:52.148
Probably a lot more yelling
than you expected.

624
00:28:52.149 --> 00:28:53.399
Maybe a little.

625
00:28:53.400 --> 00:28:57.112
Although. Bernice was Italian.
so that whole relationship was quite loud.

626
00:28:58.113 --> 00:28:59.197
Is that racist?

627
00:28:59.198 --> 00:29:01.033
Only a little.

628
00:29:01.950 --> 00:29:03.577
Hey. Jimmy. can I ask you a favor?

629
00:29:04.536 --> 00:29:07.288
I know I ruined tonight.

630
00:29:07.289 --> 00:29:10.792
but… can we try
for another first date sometime?

631
00:29:12.252 --> 00:29:13.504
Just tell me when.

632
00:29:14.171 --> 00:29:15.172
Now.

633
00:29:34.525 --> 00:29:36.484
- Hey.
- Jesus Christ.

634
00:29:36.485 --> 00:29:37.818
Why are you here so late?

635
00:29:37.819 --> 00:29:39.029
Because you are.

636
00:29:41.698 --> 00:29:43.116
Mark and Donna fired me.

637
00:29:44.993 --> 00:29:45.994
That sucks.

638
00:29:48.747 --> 00:29:49.873
What happened?

639
00:29:50.832 --> 00:29:52.333
Before they did.

640
00:29:52.334 --> 00:29:55.295
they told me that Maya had
some pretty severe abandonment issues.

641
00:29:56.380 --> 00:29:58.090
I never got that out of her. Paul.

642
00:30:01.260 --> 00:30:02.885
We can't control

643
00:30:02.886 --> 00:30:06.181
what our patients decide
not to share with us.

644
00:30:06.849 --> 00:30:09.101
No wonder she spiraled
when her friends moved away.

645
00:30:09.601 --> 00:30:12.103
You know. if I knew.
I could've done something.

646
00:30:12.104 --> 00:30:13.939
Maybe. Maybe not.

647
00:30:15.148 --> 00:30:16.733
Loneliness is a bitch.

648
00:30:18.902 --> 00:30:21.572
And it's a lonely world out there.

649
00:30:25.325 --> 00:30:27.368
You know. the worst part is not knowing

650
00:30:27.369 --> 00:30:30.247
if it was on purpose.
or if it was an accident.

651
00:30:30.914 --> 00:30:32.374
Death is death.

652
00:30:33.292 --> 00:30:38.463
Try not to beat yourself up trying
to figure out the semantics of it all.

653
00:30:39.089 --> 00:30:41.174
So you're saying
it doesn't matter if I ever know?

654
00:30:41.175 --> 00:30:43.927
I'm saying. I think you already do know.

655
00:30:49.600 --> 00:30:54.353
You know. I spent so much time
moving into trauma work.

656
00:30:54.354 --> 00:30:56.440
I never even stopped to think if I should.

657
00:30:57.357 --> 00:31:00.944
And that was a big fucking mistake
because it turns out I suck at it.

658
00:31:01.570 --> 00:31:02.863
No. you don't.

659
00:31:04.656 --> 00:31:07.158
It was an occupational hazard.

660
00:31:07.159 --> 00:31:09.160
Maya's just the first one.

661
00:31:09.161 --> 00:31:11.580
and I promise you.
if you go down this road.

662
00:31:12.623 --> 00:31:14.166
she won't be the last.

663
00:31:18.504 --> 00:31:19.629
What are you doing?

664
00:31:19.630 --> 00:31:22.049
I'm canceling all my patients
for next week.

665
00:31:22.966 --> 00:31:23.967
I changed my mind.

666
00:31:24.718 --> 00:31:25.928
I do need time off.

667
00:31:27.888 --> 00:31:30.933
Do you remember that mentor of mine
from Bellevue?

668
00:31:32.351 --> 00:31:33.935
Whenever the shit hit the fan.

669
00:31:33.936 --> 00:31:38.273
he always would say the same thing
and it really stuck with me.

670
00:31:39.858 --> 00:31:44.112
He said. "The longer it takes for you
to get back on the horse.

671
00:31:45.489 --> 00:31:49.952
the less likely it is that you will
ever be able to get back on."

672
00:31:51.370 --> 00:31:54.998
Yeah. Well. fuck the horse.

673
00:31:56.917 --> 00:31:58.168
Good night. Paul.

674
00:32:07.010 --> 00:32:08.220
Woof.
